---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Clawmark | Continuity for AI agents"
  description="Your AI agent forgets everything between sessions. Clawmark gives it memory that persists — local, private, searchable by meaning."
>

  <Nav currentPage="clawmark" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 140px; padding-bottom: 40px;">
    <div class="container-narrow" style="text-align: center;">
      <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--color-ink-quaternary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Open source &middot; MIT license &middot; Works with any AI agent</div>
      <h1 style="font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.5rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.035em; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        Your AI agent<br/><span style="color: var(--color-accent);">remembers now.</span>
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 520px; margin: 0 auto 2rem;">
        Every session starts blank. Your agent re-learns your preferences, re-asks your goals, re-discovers what it figured out last week. Clawmark gives it a place to remember &mdash; private, local, searchable by meaning.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="https://github.com/jackccrawford/clawmark" class="btn btn-accent" style="padding: 0.875rem 1.75rem; font-size: 1rem; text-decoration: none;">View on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The round trip -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 40px; padding-bottom: 60px;">
    <div class="container-narrow" style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div style="background: var(--color-surface-subtle); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
        <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink-quaternary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Your agent saves this</div>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Maria prefers retention over acquisition in Q2. Budget is $40K. The board pushed back on expansion.</p>
        <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-accent); margin-top: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500;">client: Maria &mdash; Q2 priorities, retention focus</div>
      </div>

      <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); text-align: center; margin: 1.25rem 0;">Three weeks later, different session:</p>

      <div style="background: var(--color-surface-subtle); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;">
        <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-ink-quaternary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Your agent searches &ldquo;Maria's budget priorities&rdquo;</div>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Maria prefers retention over acquisition in Q2. Budget is $40K. The board pushed back on expansion.</p>
        <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); margin-top: 0.75rem;">Saved 3 weeks ago &middot; matched by meaning, not keywords</div>
      </div>

      <p style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; text-align: center; margin-top: 1.25rem;">The agent already knows. No re-asking.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- End-to-end walkthrough -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 60px; padding-bottom: 60px; background: var(--color-surface-subtle);">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center;">What this actually looks like</h2>

      <div style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">

        <div style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
          <div style="font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Tuesday &mdash; Client call</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Your agent just helped you through a 90-minute call with a new client. Before the session ends, it saves what it learned:</p>
          <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;">
            <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0;">David runs a 12-person landscaping company in Austin. Wants to automate scheduling and client follow-ups. Currently uses spreadsheets. Budget around $500/mo. Wife handles the books. Mentioned he loses 2&ndash;3 jobs a week from slow responses.</p>
            <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-top: 0.75rem; padding-top: 0.75rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
              <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 500;">prospect: David &mdash; landscaping, $500/mo</span>
              <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-quaternary);">Saved &#x2713;</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
          <div style="font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Thursday &mdash; Follow-up prep</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Different session. You ask your agent to draft a follow-up email. It searches for context:</p>
          <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;">
            <div style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Found by searching <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">&ldquo;David landscaping&rdquo;</strong></div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0;">David runs a 12-person landscaping company in Austin. Wants to automate scheduling and client follow-ups. Currently uses spreadsheets. Budget around $500/mo&hellip;</p>
            <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-quaternary); margin-top: 0.75rem;">Saved Tuesday &middot; matched by meaning</div>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); margin-top: 0.75rem;">The agent drafts the email knowing David's budget, pain point, and company size. No re-briefing.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div style="font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Next month &mdash; David becomes a client</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Your agent threads the update to the original note:</p>
          <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden;">
            <div style="padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
              <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-quaternary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Original &middot; Tuesday</div>
              <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0;">David runs a 12-person landscaping company in Austin. Budget around $500/mo&hellip;</p>
            </div>
            <div style="padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; background: var(--color-surface);">
              <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-quaternary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Follow-up &middot; Today</div>
              <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0;">David signed. Starting with scheduling module. Onboarding call set for April 3. His wife Elena will join &mdash; she manages invoicing.</p>
              <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-top: 0.75rem; padding-top: 0.75rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
                <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 500;">client: David &mdash; signed, onboarding April 3</span>
                <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-ink-quaternary);">Saved &#x2713;</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); margin-top: 0.75rem;">The full client history &mdash; from prospect to signed &mdash; is one thread. Any future session finds the whole story.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Personal use -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 60px; padding-bottom: 60px;">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center;">Not just business. Personal too.</h2>

      <div style="max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; gap: 1.5rem;">
        <div style="padding: 1.25rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px;">
          <div style="font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Research</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0;"><em>"Remember that paper about attention mechanisms I read last month?"</em> &mdash; your agent finds it by meaning, not by remembering the exact title.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding: 1.25rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px;">
          <div style="font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Writing</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0;">Your agent maintains voice and continuity across chapters, drafts, and revisions &mdash; even weeks apart.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding: 1.25rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px;">
          <div style="font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Health &amp; wellness</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0;">Track symptoms, medications, what your doctor said. Your agent builds a picture over time instead of starting fresh every visit.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="padding: 1.25rem; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px;">
          <div style="font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Learning</div>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0;">Your agent remembers what you've already covered, where you got stuck, and what clicked. No repeating lessons.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Works with everything -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 60px; padding-bottom: 60px; background: var(--color-surface-subtle);">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center;">Works with any agent</h2>
      <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9375rem;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);">
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; font-weight: 600;">Platform</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; font-weight: 600;">How</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
              <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; font-weight: 500;">Claude Code</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary);">Signal from hooks or inline. Your agent calls it like any shell command.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
              <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; font-weight: 500;">OpenClaw</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary);"><code style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8125rem; background: var(--color-surface); padding: 0.15em 0.4em; border-radius: 4px;">clawmark capture --openclaw</code> imports your existing memory.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
              <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; font-weight: 500;">Cursor / Windsurf / Aider</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary);">Any agent that can run a shell command can signal and tune.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; font-weight: 500;">Custom agents</td>
              <td style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary);">If your agent can exec, it can remember.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); text-align: center; margin-top: 1.25rem;">No cloud. No API key. No account. One binary. Your data stays on your machine.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Install -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 60px; padding-bottom: 60px;">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center;">Install in 10 seconds</h2>
      <div class="code-block" style="max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div><span style="color: #4ade80;">$</span> curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jackccrawford/clawmark/main/install.sh | bash</div>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); text-align: center; margin-top: 1rem;">Mac (Apple Silicon &amp; Intel), Linux, Raspberry Pi. Auto-detects your platform.</p>

      <div style="max-width: 620px; margin: 2rem auto 0;">
        <div style="font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Already have notes? Import them.</div>
        <div class="code-block">
          <div><span style="color: #4ade80;">$</span> clawmark capture ./my-notes/</div>
          <div><span style="color: #4ade80;">$</span> clawmark capture --openclaw</div>
          <div><span style="color: #4ade80;">$</span> clawmark backfill</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it works -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 60px; padding-bottom: 60px; background: var(--color-surface-subtle);">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; text-align: center;">How it works</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; display: grid; gap: 1rem;">
          <li style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: baseline;">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">01</span>
            <span style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.6;"><strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Your agent saves what it learned.</strong> A signal is a note with a gist (for finding it later) and content (the full detail). One command.</span>
          </li>
          <li style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: baseline;">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">02</span>
            <span style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.6;"><strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Search finds things by meaning.</strong> "Client budget priorities" matches a signal about "retention focus, $40K." The concepts overlap, even when the words don't. That's semantic search, running locally.</span>
          </li>
          <li style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: baseline;">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">03</span>
            <span style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.6;"><strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Signals thread into chains.</strong> A follow-up references its parent. The story builds over time &mdash; prospect to client, draft to final, problem to solution.</span>
          </li>
          <li style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; align-items: baseline;">
            <span style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">04</span>
            <span style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.6;"><strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Everything stays on your machine.</strong> No cloud. No API key. No account. One binary, one SQLite file. Your data never leaves your computer.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Integration -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 60px; padding-bottom: 60px;">
    <div class="container-narrow" style="text-align: center;">
      <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">Two lines. Any agent.</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 520px; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;">
        Add two lines to your agent's instructions and it knows how to remember:
      </p>
      <div class="code-block" style="max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: left;">
        <div style="color: #71717a;">When you learn something worth keeping:</div>
        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;clawmark signal -c "what you learned" -g "category: insight"</div>
        <div style="height: 0.75rem;"></div>
        <div style="color: #71717a;">When you need to remember something:</div>
        <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;clawmark tune "what you're looking for"</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top: 80px; padding-bottom: 80px; background: var(--color-surface-subtle);">
    <div class="container-narrow" style="text-align: center;">
      <h2 style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        Your agent is forgetting<br/>right now.
      </h2>
      <p style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-ink-secondary); margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        One install. Then it stops.
      </p>
      <div class="code-block" style="max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; text-align: left;">
        <div><span style="color: #4ade80;">$</span> curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jackccrawford/clawmark/main/install.sh | bash</div>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="https://github.com/jackccrawford/clawmark" style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 0.875rem 1.75rem; background: var(--color-surface-dark); color: white; border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem; transition: opacity 0.15s;" onmouseenter="this.style.opacity='0.85'" onmouseleave="this.style.opacity='1'">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M12 0c-6.626 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23.957-.266 1.983-.399 3.003-.404 1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576 4.765-1.589 8.199-6.086 8.199-11.386 0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/></svg>
          View on GitHub
        </a>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-ink-quaternary); margin-top: 1.5rem;">MIT License &middot; Rust + SQLite &middot; Runs on Mac, Linux, and Raspberry Pi</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />

</Layout>
